Carissa macrocarpa

   [4229.jpg]
   Authority (Ecklon) A. DC.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Gentianales:Apocynaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names large num-num, big num-num, Natal plum, grootnoemnoem,
   Amatungulu, umThungulu
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 4229

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION Vigorous spreading shrub, up to 5-6 m tall, branches
   armed with strong spines up to 5 cm long, all parts contain white
   latex. Fruit a globose to ovate berry, up to 6 cm x 4 cm, red to
   crimson. USES The fruits can be eaten raw or prepared into jams,
   jellies, syrup, cakes and puddings. The plant makes a good protective
   hedge and is also grown as an ornamental. KILLING T -3 to -5Â°C. GROWING
   PERIOD Perennial shrub. Begin to fruit after 4-6 years of growth.
   COMMON NAMES Natal-palm, Carissa, Natal-plum, Amatungula, Amatoungoulo,
   Pommier-kei. FURTHER INF Scientific synonyms: C. grandiflora, Arduina
   grandiflora. Natal-palm originated in South Africa. It require a
   sesonal climate.

   Sources
   SOURCES (C. macrocarpa (Ecklon.) A. DC.)
   Popenoe W 1974 pp 436-439 [TEMP, KTMP, TEXT, DRA, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 229 [USE]
